148 Centre Street, at the S.E. corner of Walker Street (left), showing a large lot 91.7x129 in an undeveloped state. The present appearance of same has continued for over 20 years. To the left appears the side wall of the structure occupied by Moe Levy (Clothiers) for years and a feature of this vicinity.

June 10, 1938.

P. L. Sperr

(1)
Centre Street, south from Walker Street, and showing at Foley Square several civic, state and federal structures, prominent of which are, the New York State Bldg., the Federal Courts Bldg. and the Municipal Bldg. Dimly seen on the right is the old Tombs prison, opposite a clearance where a new Criminal Courts (and prison) Bldg. will rise.

P. L. Sperr

June 10, 1938.

(2)
The Tombs and the Board of Health Bldg. on the west side of Centre Street, occupying the blocks from Franklin to Worth Streets, as viewed south-westward from White Street and across the westerly side of the new court site.

P. L. Sperr

June 10, 1938.
